01:09.625 --> 01:13.000
[Rebecca Cunningham] I remember
Christmas when I was a little girl.

01:13.125 --> 01:18.333
I remember the lights,
the toys, the candy,

01:18.625 --> 01:21.625
but most of all,
I remember the snow. [sighs]

01:22.667 --> 01:24.166
You know, Molly,

01:24.250 --> 01:28.125
that's what I'd really like for Christmas,

01:28.208 --> 01:30.542
to see it snow.

01:31.208 --> 01:33.291
[Molly] Christmas isn't for two days.

01:33.375 --> 01:34.917
Maybe we'll get some.

01:35.458 --> 01:39.083
It never snows in Cape Suzette.

01:39.166 --> 01:40.917
I'm off to shop till I drop.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.125
Be good. Remember,
Santa's checking his list.

01:44.375 --> 01:45.834
[Baloo] [chuckles] Later, Becky.

01:45.917 --> 01:47.458
Bye, Mom.

01:50.500 --> 01:53.000
[Wildcat] Hey, Baloo, check it out.

01:53.709 --> 01:56.041
Now that's what I like to see--

01:58.125 --> 02:00.792
A guy who gets into his work.

02:01.959 --> 02:03.000
Hi, pumpkin.

02:03.083 --> 02:04.625
Going to help us decorate?

02:04.834 --> 02:06.875
Nope, writing Santa.

02:06.959 --> 02:10.583
You already sent him one.
No fair writing two.

02:10.667 --> 02:14.375
[Molly] This is a special-delivery
emergency letter.

02:15.458 --> 02:17.583
My last candy cane!

02:17.667 --> 02:22.375
Well now, we might be able to do
something about this.

02:22.625 --> 02:25.375
Hmm...

02:25.458 --> 02:26.458
Yep.

02:27.125 --> 02:29.583
This is the one to put under your pillow.

02:29.792 --> 02:30.917
What for?

02:31.166 --> 02:32.917
For the Peppermint Fairy.

02:33.417 --> 02:35.000
Oh, Baloo.

02:35.083 --> 02:37.166
You've heard of the tooth fairy.

02:37.500 --> 02:39.458
Well, this is her cousin.

02:39.542 --> 02:40.500
Really?

02:40.667 --> 02:42.500
Wow! Thanks, Baloo.

02:45.250 --> 02:48.125
Better remember to slip a candy cane
under her pillow tonight.

02:51.875 --> 02:54.208
[cock-a-doodle-do]

02:55.500 --> 02:56.583
[Rebecca Cunningham] Wake up, Baloo.

02:56.667 --> 02:58.125
It's an emergency.

02:58.208 --> 03:00.125
What? What?

03:00.208 --> 03:02.083
The store gave me the wrong present.

03:02.166 --> 03:05.166
I wanted a nutcracker,
not a vegetable slicer.

03:05.333 --> 03:09.500
Get that soap shipment loaded
and watch Molly.

03:09.750 --> 03:14.125
Load Molly on the plane-- [mumbles]

03:17.834 --> 03:18.750
Molly!

03:19.959 --> 03:22.542
Oh! Candy cane! Candy cane!

03:22.917 --> 03:24.375
Don't tell me you forgot.

03:29.792 --> 03:32.041
[Baloo] Peppermint Fairy to the rescue!

03:43.291 --> 03:46.709
Did the Peppermint Fairy forget something?

03:46.792 --> 03:48.041
Oh, hi.

03:48.125 --> 03:50.959
The Peppermint Fairy told me to--

03:51.333 --> 03:53.000
There's no Peppermint Fairy.

03:53.083 --> 03:54.917
You lied to a little kid.

03:55.083 --> 03:56.792
I was only trying--

03:56.875 --> 04:01.000
I bet that Santa stuff is baloney, too.

04:01.083 --> 04:04.500
Oh, no, Molly, Santa hates baloney.

04:04.583 --> 04:08.000
How can I write Santa
if there is no Santa?

04:08.583 --> 04:10.417
Now, wait a minute.

04:14.041 --> 04:17.208
Of course there's a Santa Claus.

04:17.291 --> 04:19.208
Yeah? Prove it.

04:19.291 --> 04:21.375
OK, I will.

04:21.458 --> 04:23.709
I'm flying you to the North Pole.

04:23.792 --> 04:26.417
You can give your letter
to Santa in person.

04:26.875 --> 04:27.792
Really?

04:28.333 --> 04:31.041
Really. Get your coat on.
We got to hurry...

04:31.250 --> 04:33.041
Before Rebecca gets back.

04:33.375 --> 04:35.041
What are you doing?

04:35.500 --> 04:37.834
Don't worry, Kit. Papa Bear's got a plan.

04:40.917 --> 04:43.000
[Louie] Louie's place. It's your dime.

04:43.208 --> 04:45.500
Why, deck the halls, it's Baloo.

04:46.125 --> 04:48.917
Of course I know it's Christmas.

04:49.291 --> 04:51.500
Sure, I'll do you a favor.
What have you got?

04:53.083 --> 04:55.458
You want me to dress up as <i>who?</i>

05:01.959 --> 05:04.083
[Wildcat] OK, Mr. Soap flakes,

05:04.166 --> 05:06.959
you're going on a big trip.

05:09.083 --> 05:11.709
[Baloo] Sorry, Wildcat, no time for cargo.

05:11.792 --> 05:13.417
We're taking off.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.333
[Wildcat] You really are
going to the north pole?

05:17.625 --> 05:18.583
Yep.

05:18.667 --> 05:22.208
I'll put in a good word
for you with Santa.

05:22.291 --> 05:26.667
That's great, but take me.
I won't say anything.

05:26.792 --> 05:30.458
I'll sit quietly.
I'll be quiet in the backseat.

05:31.834 --> 05:33.291
[birds calling]

05:36.208 --> 05:37.166
[Molly] Can I look yet?

05:37.417 --> 05:38.375
Not yet.

05:38.667 --> 05:40.291
You'll spoil the surprise.

05:43.000 --> 05:44.125
[Waldo] Santa's place.

05:44.208 --> 05:45.250
Who's there?

05:45.709 --> 05:47.667
Letter for Mr. Claus.

05:47.750 --> 05:49.667
Well, come right in.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.041
Wow!

05:59.709 --> 06:01.291
[Baloo] What did I tell you?

06:04.959 --> 06:06.959
Look! Reindeer!

06:08.208 --> 06:11.375
What did you expect in the North Pole?

06:11.458 --> 06:15.083
-[sleigh bells]
-Gee, Molly, what's that?

06:15.250 --> 06:18.583
[Baloo] Man, you don't suppose...

06:19.792 --> 06:21.417
Do you think it could be?

06:27.834 --> 06:29.125
It is!

06:29.208 --> 06:30.792
[Louie] <i>♪ Heigh-dee, heigh-dee</i>
<i>Heigh-dee, heigh-dee ♪</i>

06:31.041 --> 06:34.417
<i>♪ Heigh-dee, ho ho ho, doo-wah ♪</i>

06:34.500 --> 06:36.250
Ix-nay on the ive-jay.

06:36.333 --> 06:37.458
[clears throat]

06:37.667 --> 06:42.291
Santa, I brought a very special friend
of mine to meet you.

06:43.750 --> 06:45.000
Mwa!

06:45.375 --> 06:46.458
Don't tell me.

06:46.542 --> 06:47.792
Molly, right?

06:48.375 --> 06:50.458
And a cool yule to you, too.

06:51.333 --> 06:53.542
Hello, Santa, I brought--

06:53.625 --> 06:56.125
Elf Waldo, my list!

06:56.667 --> 06:57.625
Let me see--

06:57.709 --> 06:59.000
[Louie] Dolly, Holly, Solly, Polly...

06:59.083 --> 07:00.250
Molly!

07:00.417 --> 07:03.125
This kid's grade "a," triple gold star,

07:03.208 --> 07:04.250
<i>numero uno </i> good!

07:04.625 --> 07:07.333
So I'll get what I want?

07:07.417 --> 07:10.458
Santa will give you everything you want.

07:10.542 --> 07:12.000
Hang on.

07:12.208 --> 07:14.959
OK, now, take a couple of these
and some of these.

07:15.041 --> 07:16.000
But--

07:16.083 --> 07:17.917
[Louie] A few of those.

07:18.041 --> 07:20.000
Check this out. You'll love that.

07:20.083 --> 07:23.291
[unclear] Don't even need a battery.
Makes a face.

07:24.709 --> 07:26.166
Here you go.

07:26.542 --> 07:29.125
Some of this, some of that.
You'll love this.

07:29.208 --> 07:31.458
[scatting] Do your own soundtrack.

07:31.542 --> 07:32.792
Have a couple, and--

07:32.875 --> 07:34.792
Did I forget this one?

07:35.250 --> 07:36.417
[Molly] Uh, Mr. Claus--

07:36.500 --> 07:37.959
Oh, that's OK.

07:38.041 --> 07:39.959
I promised I'd give you what you wanted,
didn't I?

07:40.041 --> 07:41.458
[Molly] But Mr. Santa--

07:41.542 --> 07:45.250
Remember, be real good
'cause Santa's watching.

07:45.625 --> 07:47.375
Oh, yeah. Merry Christmas!

07:47.709 --> 07:49.458
Ho ho and stuff like that.

07:49.542 --> 07:51.291
[Molly] Santa, please wait!

07:51.750 --> 07:52.959
Thank you, but...

07:53.375 --> 07:56.333
I really wanted to give you this letter.

07:56.625 --> 07:58.458
A-A letter?

07:58.542 --> 07:59.834
For me?

08:00.250 --> 08:02.834
Oh, ain't she sweet?

08:03.291 --> 08:06.542
Lay it on us, oh, Waldo elf.

08:07.291 --> 08:08.291
[Waldo] "Dear Santa,

08:08.458 --> 08:11.834
I only want one present this year.
It's not for me.

08:12.166 --> 08:14.709
It's for my mom.

08:15.750 --> 08:18.166
Could you make it snow for her?

08:18.250 --> 08:22.125
That would be the biggest
and bestest present of all.

08:22.375 --> 08:23.834
Love, Molly."

08:24.250 --> 08:26.125
Hmm.

08:26.208 --> 08:27.583
Uh, ha ha.

08:27.667 --> 08:29.542
Your wish is Santa's command,

08:29.750 --> 08:31.041
that's for sure.

08:31.250 --> 08:34.000
Excuse me a minute, pumpkin.

08:34.082 --> 08:36.917
You said Santa Claus, not Jack Frost.

08:37.000 --> 08:39.207
What are we going to do now?

08:41.875 --> 08:44.875
What you mean, keep her Santafied
a couple hours?

08:45.208 --> 08:47.417
Easy, man, I've got a plan.

08:47.500 --> 08:51.625
Kit and I will get
that cargo of soap flakes.

08:52.041 --> 08:54.083
We buzz back, shake out the soap,

08:54.166 --> 08:56.667
and Molly will see snow.

08:56.750 --> 08:59.792
No, I am one retired Santa.

09:00.041 --> 09:04.917
Oh, come on! You want to ruin
Christmas for a kid?

09:05.417 --> 09:07.458
Think what the real Santa would say.

09:07.792 --> 09:09.917
Oh... [groans]

09:10.208 --> 09:11.458
Keep her busy.

09:11.542 --> 09:13.291
Sing carols or something.

09:13.375 --> 09:15.125
What if customers show up?

09:15.208 --> 09:16.875
Have them sing, too.

09:17.208 --> 09:18.333
Crazy.

09:19.875 --> 09:23.166
OK, Molly,
while we're waiting for the snow--

09:23.250 --> 09:25.709
it will be here any minute, I bet.
[chuckles]

09:26.041 --> 09:28.959
we're going to lay some
<i>Jingle Bells </i> on you.

09:29.417 --> 09:30.250
We are?

09:30.333 --> 09:31.333
We are.

09:31.417 --> 09:33.667
Uh-one, and uh-two.

09:33.750 --> 09:36.458
<i>♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells ♪</i>

09:36.709 --> 09:39.125
<i>♪ Jingle all the way ♪</i>

09:39.500 --> 09:41.917
<i>♪ Oh, what fun it is to ride ♪</i>

09:42.083 --> 09:44.959
<i>♪ In a one-horse open sleigh, hey ♪</i>

09:45.291 --> 09:47.875
<i>♪ Jingle bells jingle bells ♪</i>

09:48.208 --> 09:50.834
<i>♪ Jingle all the way ♪</i>

09:51.041 --> 09:53.291
<i>♪ Oh, what fun it is to ride ♪</i>

09:53.375 --> 09:55.375
<i>♪ In a one-horse open... ♪</i>

09:55.709 --> 09:57.125
[slurred singing] <i>♪ Jingle bells ♪</i>

09:57.291 --> 10:00.166
<i>♪ Jingle all the way ♪</i>

10:00.333 --> 10:01.959
<i>♪ Oh, what fun-- ♪</i>

10:02.041 --> 10:04.834
[Don Karnage] Shut up
with the jingle-belling.

10:05.667 --> 10:08.208
Visions of plunder danced through my head,

10:08.291 --> 10:10.000
and you woke me up!

10:10.125 --> 10:11.208
What's your problem?

10:12.000 --> 10:15.125
We're getting nothing for Christmas.

10:16.125 --> 10:19.417
Yeah. On account that we've been real bad.

10:20.875 --> 10:22.500
[Gibber whispering]

10:22.583 --> 10:23.583
What do you mean

10:23.667 --> 10:26.041
next year you're going to be good?

10:26.125 --> 10:28.625
You hooligans! Bad ids good!

10:29.500 --> 10:34.125
But, let us not be the hasty puddings.

10:34.500 --> 10:36.500
You want Christmas presents?

10:36.959 --> 10:38.583
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:38.834 --> 10:42.125
Is this not the season of giving?

10:42.333 --> 10:44.125
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:44.500 --> 10:46.750
Then, my plundering pirates,

10:46.834 --> 10:50.166
we'll make people give presents to us.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.250
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:52.875 --> 10:54.041
To the planes!

10:54.208 --> 10:55.750
Let's go!

10:56.083 --> 10:57.667
I'm not usually generous,

10:57.834 --> 11:00.458
but Christmas comes only once a year.

11:04.375 --> 11:07.125
[engine idling and revving]

11:09.917 --> 11:10.834
Wildcat?

11:11.875 --> 11:13.875
Why is the cargo still here?

11:14.000 --> 11:14.959
Where is the <i>Sea Duck?</i>

11:15.166 --> 11:16.000
Well--

11:16.083 --> 11:18.125
Where are Baloo and Kit?

11:18.625 --> 11:19.875
Uh...

11:20.125 --> 11:21.500
And where's Molly?

11:21.709 --> 11:24.375
They took her to the North Pole

11:24.458 --> 11:27.792
to see Santa Claus and left me here.

11:30.291 --> 11:33.291
-How do you work this thing?
-[ <i>Sea Duck </i> landing]

11:36.417 --> 11:37.500
Hi, Becky.

11:37.583 --> 11:38.750
Bye, Becky.

11:40.792 --> 11:41.667
Oops.

11:41.750 --> 11:45.834
What are you doing with my soap flakes?

11:46.125 --> 11:48.500
We wanted to sprinkle
them from the plane--

11:48.709 --> 11:49.625
What?

11:50.083 --> 11:52.917
Molly asked Santa to make it snow
for her mom.

11:53.083 --> 11:55.917
You know... for a Christmas present.

11:56.750 --> 12:00.166
Baloo's trying to make her wish come true.

12:01.333 --> 12:02.709
Oh, Baloo.

12:03.917 --> 12:06.625
Oh, Baloo is right. A storm.

12:06.959 --> 12:08.875
What else will go wrong?

12:09.000 --> 12:10.875
[crowd clamoring]

12:12.458 --> 12:15.834
Come on, Waldo.
We always spend Christmas eve here.

12:15.917 --> 12:18.166
How long are you gonna
keep us here in the rain?

12:18.667 --> 12:19.959
We're not ready yet.

12:20.250 --> 12:24.125
[stammers]
We're getting the decorations ready.

12:24.667 --> 12:25.750
<i>♪ Jingle bells... ♪</i>

12:25.875 --> 12:27.291
You hear that?

12:27.375 --> 12:29.709
The party started without us.
Come on, boys.

12:29.917 --> 12:31.083
[all screaming]

12:33.041 --> 12:36.417
<i>♪ Jingle bells jingle bells... ♪</i>

12:36.583 --> 12:38.583
What the matter, sugarplum?

12:39.083 --> 12:42.792
Santa, um, are you going
to make it snow soon?

12:42.959 --> 12:47.041
Oh, yeah. I-- ha ha, ho ho,
any minute now.

12:47.166 --> 12:50.667
Santa's got to get
into the right Jingle Bell mood.

12:51.583 --> 12:53.583
OK, one more time.

12:54.083 --> 12:56.083
Uh-one, and uh-two...

12:56.166 --> 12:59.041
[Baloo]
<i>Undercover elf-calling the North Pole.</i>

12:59.125 --> 13:02.000
-[static]
<i>-Undercover elf calling the North Pole.</i>

13:02.125 --> 13:04.250
<i>You read me, Santa?</i>

13:05.041 --> 13:08.458
The biggest and best
Christmas present of all

13:08.625 --> 13:11.000
is on the way.

13:11.208 --> 13:14.291
[Louie] <i>Santa digs you loud</i>
<i>and clear, Rudolph.</i>

13:14.834 --> 13:17.750
Whoo! Over easy and out.

13:18.166 --> 13:20.709
Put on your mittens, Molly-kittens.

13:20.792 --> 13:23.083
Santa's got snow to go.

13:23.417 --> 13:24.291
Yippee!

13:27.583 --> 13:32.000
[Don Karnage] Yes, Don Karnage,
there is a Santa Claus.

13:32.417 --> 13:35.083
Did you hear, my merry marauders?

13:35.166 --> 13:38.041
The best Christmas present of all!

13:38.333 --> 13:40.458
We have hit the jack in the pot!

13:45.917 --> 13:47.750
[Kit Cloudkicker] About 10 miles out.

13:48.000 --> 13:49.208
Coming in!

13:49.417 --> 13:52.166
[Baloo] Stand by for Operation Snow Storm.

13:52.250 --> 13:53.625
-Ready!
-Ready!

13:53.709 --> 13:54.959
[Gunshots]

13:55.041 --> 13:56.250
Aah!

13:57.583 --> 13:58.583
Pirates.

13:58.875 --> 14:01.542
[Don Karnage] <i>Merry Christmas,</i>
<i>Baloo-type of person.</i>

14:01.834 --> 14:04.625
<i>It is I, Santa Karnage.</i>

14:04.834 --> 14:06.834
You will fill our stockings

14:06.834 --> 14:09.667
with your biggest
and bestest present of all,

14:10.583 --> 14:13.458
or we will blast you to tinsel.

14:53.125 --> 14:56.959
See here, Don Garbage, it's Christmas eve.

14:57.083 --> 14:58.917
It's my daughter's present.

14:59.250 --> 15:01.959
She has a point on her head.

15:03.000 --> 15:06.166
I'd be stealing candy canes from a baby.

15:06.834 --> 15:08.542
I love that!

15:08.625 --> 15:09.875
Attack!

15:11.500 --> 15:16.125
Baloo! We can't outrun him in this storm!
What are we going to do?

15:16.625 --> 15:18.291
Only thing we can do.

15:21.208 --> 15:24.250
OK, Karnie, you want a present?
You got it.

15:24.417 --> 15:28.500
Ah, good. They are trembling in fear.

15:29.000 --> 15:31.208
[Baloo] <i>Get ready. Here it comes.</i>

15:31.625 --> 15:33.625
Merry Christmas!

15:33.750 --> 15:35.417
Merry Christmas!

15:35.500 --> 15:37.291
Merry Christmas!

15:42.625 --> 15:44.792
[motors clunking]

16:00.291 --> 16:02.291
That's it! We got them!

16:02.375 --> 16:04.667
Save the rest for Molly!

16:04.750 --> 16:05.709
Aah!

16:06.166 --> 16:07.166
Aah!

16:09.625 --> 16:12.500
Wildcat, close the hatch!

16:16.375 --> 16:17.625
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

16:26.583 --> 16:29.000
Oh, boy! Ha ha ha!

16:29.083 --> 16:30.208
Snow!

16:30.291 --> 16:31.542
[Dumptruck] Ha ha ha!

16:31.625 --> 16:33.041
[all laughing]

16:43.125 --> 16:44.667
We lost it all?

16:44.750 --> 16:46.625
No, I saved one.

16:50.041 --> 16:52.667
